      • addBuildResultContributions

        IBuildResult addBuildResultContributions(IBuildResultHandle buildResultHandle,
                                         IBuildResultContribution[] buildResultContributions,
                                         java.lang.String[] properties,
                                         org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                                  throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                         java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Adds the specified build result contributions to the given build result. The build result itself will only be modified under two conditions:
        1. The build result does not yet reference a container that is used to store the contributions.
        2. One of the contributions indicates that it impacts the primary result and has a BuildStatus of greater severity than the status of the specified build result.
        Parameters:
        buildResultHandle - The build result to add the contributions to.
        buildResultContributions - The build result contributions to add to the build result.
        properties - The properties to return in the build result if it's modified.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        The build result with the specified properties that the contributions were added to.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs while accessing the repository.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If buildResultHandle or any member of the buildResultContributions or properties array is null.

      • deleteBuildResultContributions

        void deleteBuildResultContributions(IBuildResultHandle buildResultHandle,
                                    IBuildResultContribution[] buildResultContributions,
                                    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                             throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                    java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Deletes the specified build result contributions from the given build result. The contributions must be instances that were returned by a call to getBuildResultContributions(IBuildResultHandle, String, IProgressMonitor) or getBuildResultContributions(IBuildResultHandle, String[], IProgressMonitor). The deletion of contributions will have no automatic impact on the status of the build result. It's up to the client to determine if the deletion warrants a change in the status of the build result.
        Parameters:
        buildResultHandle - The build result to remove the contributions from.
        buildResultContributions - The build result contributions to remove from the build result.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs while accessing the repository.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If buildResultHandle or any member of the buildResultContributions array is null.

      • startBuildActivity

        java.lang.String startBuildActivity(IBuildResultHandle buildResultHandle,
                                    java.lang.String label,
                                    java.lang.String parentId,
                                    boolean autoComplete,
                                    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                             throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                    java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Start a build activity with the label in the specified build result. Returns a unique id for the newly started activity.

        If parentId is set, the new activity is created as a child of the existing activity with that id.

        If autoComplete is true, then this activity will be automatically completed when either the build is completed, this activity's parent activity is completed or when the next peer activity is started.

        Parameters:
        buildResultHandle - The build result to start the activity in.
        label - The label describing the activity.
        parentId - Optional id of a parent activity.
        autoComplete - Whether or not to automatically complete this activity.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        The unique id of the new activity.
        Throws:
        TeamBuildStateException - If the build is not currently in progress.
        TeamBuildException - If parentId is set but an activity with that id is not found or is found but has already completed.
        TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs while accessing the repository.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If buildResultHandle or label is null, or if label is empty.

      • getInProgressActivityLabel

        java.lang.String getInProgressActivityLabel(IBuildResultHandle buildResultHandle,
                                            org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                                     throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                            java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Deprecated. Use getBuildActivities(IBuildResultHandle, IProgressMonitor) to traverse the activities to present an appropriate in progress activity label. It will be removed in a future iteration.
        Retrieves the in progress activity label for the specified build result. The text will be one of the following:
        1. No activity in progress - an empty string will be returned.
        2. Single activity in progress - The label of that activity will be returned.
        3. Multiple activities in progress - the text "multiple activities" will be returned.
        Parameters:
        buildResultHandle - The build result to retrieve the build activities from.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        Text representing the in progress activities.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs while accessing the repository.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If buildResultHandle is null.

      • getPercentComplete

        int getPercentComplete(IBuildResultHandle buildResultHandle,
                       org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                throws TeamRepositoryException,
                       java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Deprecated. Use a combination of getBuildActivities(IBuildResultHandle, IProgressMonitor) and IBuildDefinition.getBuildAverageData() to compute the percent complete. This method will be removed in a future iteration. It's use is not encouraged.

      • anyResponsiveBuildEngines

        boolean anyResponsiveBuildEngines(IBuildDefinitionHandle buildDefinitionHandle,
                                  org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                           throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                  java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Determines if there are any responsive active engines that support the specified build definition. An engine is considered responsive if any of the following conditions are met:

        • The engine is not participating in last contact threshold monitoring.
        • The engine is currently busy doing another build.
        • The difference between the last time the engine contacted the repository and the time this method is invoked does not exceed the monitoring threshold.
          • .
        Parameters:
        buildDefinitionHandle - The build definitions to determine if there are any responsive engines for.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        true if at least one engine supporting the specified definition is considered responsive.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs while accessing the repository.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildDefinitionHandle is null.

      • anyBuildEnginesWithRequestProcessingEnabled

        boolean anyBuildEnginesWithRequestProcessingEnabled(IBuildDefinitionHandle buildDefinitionHandle,
                                                    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                                             throws TeamRepositoryException,
                                                    java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Determines if there are any active engines that support the specified build definition and have request processing enabled.

        If a definition has no supporting build engines with request processing enabled, then builds for that definition should not be scheduled or manually requested because the requests will never be processed.

        Parameters:
        buildDefinitionHandle - The build definition to determine if there are any request-processing-enabled engines for.
        progressMonitor - The progress monitor to track progress on or null if progress monitoring is not desired.
        Returns:
        true if at least one engine supporting the specified definition supports request processing
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - If an error occurs while accessing the repository.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the buildDefinitionHandle is null.
